Definitions

The information in this section aims to summarise programme entry over time. This may be presented by treatment initiation or first consultation. Counts are split into calendar months or quarters and are tabulated and graphically represented. For comparison with more recent information, tables summarising monthly inclusions over the life of a programme are included.

Definition

Table
Summarises the number and percentage of patients included in the cohort by calendar month. Episodes (e.g. treatment initation or pregnancy), rather than individual patients, are counted in this table.

Monthly & Quarterly plots
Monthly and quarterly bar plots visually display programme entry by time period. These counts may be segregated further in some reports (e.g. TB treatment type). This type of plot should quickly illustrate seasonal or temporal changes in programme inclusion

Maternal age and gestation
Programme entry has been stratified into maternal age categories and trimester at first consultation. Tremesters have been defined as 0-12 weeks, 13-27 weeks and 28-40 weeks. Gestation is presented as <i>post-partum</i> after 40 weeks. Gestation at admission to the PMTCT programme is calculated from the PMTCT admission date and the date of delivery. Gestation is recorded as missing where one of these dates is not entered. Three reporting periods have been included - the reporting period defined by the user, the 12 months prior to the end of the user-defined reporting period, and the full programme duration.

Key variables

Admission cohort inclusion: Date of PMTCT admission
Delivery cohort inclusion: Date of delivery

Definitions

This section provides a summary of the number of deliveries within the programme, their outcomes and information about the infant's immediate HIV care.

Definition

Deliveries
The number of deliveries within the programme are tabulated and plotted by month and quarter. Delivery type and the number of live births is recorded for each reporting period. Three reporting periods have been included - the reporting period defined by the user, the 12 months prior to the end of the user-defined reporting period, and the full programme duration..

Infants
Where a live infant was born, HIV prophylaxis type and breastfeeding status are summarised.

Plot

Definitions

Early Infant Diagnosis should be performed before 12 weeks of life using an age-appropriate test.

Definition

EID performed
This is a process indicator which establishes the proportion of all live births who were tested for HIV prior to 12 weeks of age. The indicator requires an HIV assessment date within 12 weeks of birth with a molecular HIV test type being recorded. A record of an HIV test result is not required for this indicator.

EID results
This quality indicator describes the proportion of infants tested who had a positive result. Indeterminate, unknown or unavailable results are recorded as missing.

Definitions

The PMTCT programme outcome is given 18 months after delivery to allow sufficient time for infants to be tested for HIV using an antigen/antibody test. Infants may continue to be exposed to HIV through breastfeeding, but for convenience of reporting, outcomes are attributed 18 months after delivery.

Definition

Final HIV status
The final HIV test result recorded for each infant

Final programme outcome
The final programme outcome recorded for each infant.
